  <h1>Service Dog Requirements & Standards</h1>

  <h2>ADA Task Requirements</h2>
  <p>Service dogs must perform <strong>specific tasks</strong> that:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Directly relate to your disability</li>
    <li>Are actively trained behaviors (not natural behaviors)</li>
    <li>Mitigate specific disability-related limitations</li>
    <li>Can be demonstrated if challenged</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Examples of Valid Tasks for Veterans:</h3>
  <ul class="advantage-list">
    <li><strong>Nightmare Interruption:</strong> Tactile stimulation to wake from nightmares</li>
    <li><strong>Room Clearing:</strong> Safety checks before entering spaces</li>
    <li><strong>Crowd Control:</strong> Space buffering in crowded areas</li>
    <li><strong>Panic Attack Interruption:</strong> Deep pressure therapy during episodes</li>
    <li><strong>Medication Reminders:</strong> Alerting at scheduled times</li>
    <li><strong>Balance Support:</strong> Bracing for mobility assistance</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Public Access Standards</h2>
  <div class="alert alert-info">
    <strong>Required Behaviors for Public Access:</strong>
  </div>

  <ul class="check-list">
    <li>‚úÖ <strong>Controlled Entry/Exit:</strong> Calmly enters and exits buildings without pulling</li>
    <li>‚úÖ <strong>Heeling:</strong> Maintains position beside handler in all environments</li>
    <li>‚úÖ <strong>Sit/Down/Stay:</strong> Holds position for extended periods (30+ minutes)</li>
    <li>‚úÖ <strong>Recall:</strong> Returns immediately when called, even with distractions</li>
    <li>‚úÖ <strong>Ignore Distractions:</strong> No reaction to food, people, animals, sounds</li>
    <li>‚úÖ <strong>No Solicitation:</strong> Does not seek attention from public</li>
    <li>‚úÖ <strong>Toilet on Command:</strong> Only eliminates when given specific cue</li>
    <li>‚úÖ <strong>No Vocalization:</strong> Remains quiet in public settings</li>
    <li>‚úÖ <strong>Appropriate Behavior:</strong> No jumping, sniffing, or inappropriate contact</li>
  </ul>

